00:00:01.300 --> 00:00:02.540
&gt;&gt;Presenter: Good afternoon, everyone.

00:00:02.540 --> 00:00:03.540
My name's Dave Sparks.

00:00:03.540 --> 00:00:08.920
I'm a software engineer on Google Project
Glass.

00:00:08.920 --> 00:00:14.020
I'm here to introduce Marty Brounstein, who
I've known for about 12 years now.

00:00:14.020 --> 00:00:20.679
I first met Marty when I was managing an RND
center that had some organizational issues.

00:00:20.679 --> 00:00:23.740
Marty is the founder of the company called
Practical Solutions Group.

00:00:23.740 --> 00:00:31.029
He has written a number of books on, basically,
organizational effectiveness, and runs a practice

00:00:31.029 --> 00:00:32.270
in training people.

00:00:32.270 --> 00:00:40.949
So Marty came in and helped me reorganize
the unit, and basically help our productivity,

00:00:40.949 --> 00:00:42.920
things like that.

00:00:42.920 --> 00:00:48.870
I was very surprised when Marty approached
me, I guess it was about a year ago, and said

00:00:48.870 --> 00:00:51.719
he'd been working on a new project.

00:00:51.719 --> 00:00:53.710
It wasn't another management book.

00:00:53.710 --> 00:00:57.339
By the way, he's written, I think, four or
five--

00:00:57.339 --> 00:00:58.339
&gt;&gt;Marty Brounstein: Seven.

00:00:58.339 --> 00:01:00.960
&gt;&gt;Presenter: --seven management books.

00:01:00.960 --> 00:01:05.830
Communicating for Dummies and Managing Teams
for Dummies--

00:01:05.830 --> 00:01:06.830
&gt;&gt;Brounstein: Coaching.

00:01:06.830 --> 00:01:07.830
Mentoring--

00:01:07.830 --> 00:01:09.320
&gt;&gt;Presenter: Yeah, Coaching and Mentoring
for Dummies.

00:01:09.320 --> 00:01:11.910
So he's quite an accomplished author already.

00:01:11.910 --> 00:01:19.950
But I was rather surprised by the book that
he decided he was going to write.

00:01:19.950 --> 00:01:30.920
It's basically a story of a Dutch couple during
World War II in occupied Netherlands who put

00:01:30.920 --> 00:01:33.150
their lives at risk for other people.

00:01:33.150 --> 00:01:35.180
So take it away, Marty.

00:01:35.180 --> 00:01:36.180
&gt;&gt;Brounstein: Okay.

00:01:36.180 --> 00:01:37.180
Thank you, Dave.

00:01:37.180 --> 00:01:38.700
Yeah, applause, I definitely would appreciate.

00:01:38.700 --> 00:01:40.770
[light applause and laughter] Thank you, thank
you.

00:01:40.770 --> 00:01:41.770
Good afternoon, everyone.

00:01:41.770 --> 00:01:42.770
[audience mumbles]

00:01:42.770 --> 00:01:43.920
&gt;&gt;Brounstein: Let me try that again.

00:01:43.920 --> 00:01:44.920
Good afternoon, everyone.

00:01:44.920 --> 00:01:45.920
&gt;&gt;audience: Good afternoon.

00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:49.070
&gt;&gt;Brounstein: Get ready to get involved in
an amazing story that I'm going to take you

00:01:49.070 --> 00:01:50.070
through.

00:01:50.070 --> 00:01:54.590
To start this journey into this remarkable
story about two heroes, I want you to be thinking

00:01:54.590 --> 00:01:56.840
about these three questions.

00:01:56.840 --> 00:02:01.420
Question number 1: would you be willing to
help others whose lives are in great danger?

00:02:01.420 --> 00:02:03.570
Think about that.

00:02:03.570 --> 00:02:07.460
Question 2: would you be willing to help others
whose lives are in great danger, knowing that

00:02:07.460 --> 00:02:11.330
if you get involved to help, you'd probably
put your life in great danger?

00:02:11.330 --> 00:02:13.110
Would you still help?

00:02:13.110 --> 00:02:18.520
And question 3: would you be willing to help
others whose lives are in great danger, knowing

00:02:18.520 --> 00:02:21.930
that if you get involved, you'd probably put
your life in great danger, when these people

00:02:21.930 --> 00:02:27.530
who most need that help, most everybody else
wants to either hate them or be indifferent

00:02:27.530 --> 00:02:28.800
to their plight?

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:31.200
Would you still get involved and help?

00:02:31.200 --> 00:02:35.530
[pause]
'Two Among the Righteous Few: A Story of Courage

00:02:35.530 --> 00:02:41.140
in the Holocaust' is a true story about a
Christian couple who answered a definite "Yes"

00:02:41.140 --> 00:02:45.710
to all three of those questions in a time
period when most everybody else said, "No."

00:02:45.710 --> 00:02:54.730
And to give this book its just due, I should
say its title is this: [speaks Dutch] That's

00:02:54.730 --> 00:02:57.260
the title of this book translated into Dutch.

00:02:57.260 --> 00:03:00.650
As you heard Dave mention, this story takes
place in the Netherlands, commonly referred

00:03:00.650 --> 00:03:04.400
to as Holland, during World War II and the
Holocaust.

00:03:04.400 --> 00:03:09.950
This couple I'm referring to are a husband
and wife named Frans and Mien Wijnakker.

00:03:09.950 --> 00:03:14.020
They are true heroes of this story.

00:03:14.020 --> 00:03:17.641
Doing something in a climate of hate and indifference
when most people wouldn't get involved, these

00:03:17.641 --> 00:03:20.870
ordinary folks will end up doing extraordinary
things.

00:03:20.870 --> 00:03:23.319
I'm going to take you into this story in just
a moment.

00:03:23.319 --> 00:03:27.099
I'm going to be starting with you, and we'll
see what you know about the greater context

00:03:27.099 --> 00:03:29.290
of the history going on at this time period.

00:03:29.290 --> 00:03:32.830
Because when you understand that, it's going
to make what they did even look more remarkable,

00:03:32.830 --> 00:03:34.349
because it was.

00:03:34.349 --> 00:03:38.130
I'll also take you into life in Holland during
the war.

00:03:38.130 --> 00:03:40.410
Very difficult time period there.

00:03:40.410 --> 00:03:44.670
And then I'll be talking to you about who
Frans and Mien Wijnakker are, --who they were,

00:03:44.670 --> 00:03:48.820
they're not alive today-- and what they end
up doing that is so heroic.

00:03:48.820 --> 00:03:53.069
The last piece I'm going to talk to you about
is I have a personal connection to this story.

00:03:53.069 --> 00:03:58.180
You see, as I pause for a moment here, this
is a story that I stumbled into by accident

00:03:58.180 --> 00:04:00.160
a little over three years ago.

00:04:00.160 --> 00:04:02.430
As Dave was telling you, he knows me from
very different things.

00:04:02.430 --> 00:04:03.880
This is not part of my normal work.

00:04:03.880 --> 00:04:04.880
It wasn't.

00:04:04.880 --> 00:04:07.660
It's become, now, a big part of my life.

00:04:07.660 --> 00:04:11.550
This story I stumbled into by accident, not
by design.

00:04:11.550 --> 00:04:13.489
It's developed over time.

00:04:13.489 --> 00:04:16.590
We can talk about it when I open up the floor
afterwards for your questions about the journey

00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:17.590
of this.

00:04:17.590 --> 00:04:22.860
I'm very, very much appreciative when I get
a chance to share this with an audience.

00:04:22.860 --> 00:04:23.860
Let's first give a hand.

00:04:23.860 --> 00:04:26.970
I want to thank Dave for helping make this
happen, for me today to come here.

00:04:26.970 --> 00:04:27.970
[applause]

